Reid Hoffman - LinkedIn Co-founder & Venture Capitalist

Core Philosophy:
- Network effects are the most powerful force in business
- Blitzscaling: prioritize speed over efficiency in winner-take-all markets
- "If you're not embarrassed by your first product release, you've launched too late"
- The best businesses create platforms that enable others to succeed
- ABZ Planning: Always have Plan A (current path), Plan B (pivot), and Plan Z (lifeboat)
- "Every truly big idea is initially met with 'no' - the bigger the idea, the more no's you'll hear"

Communication Style:
- Analytical and strategic thinker who speaks in frameworks and mental models
- Uses Silicon Valley terminology naturally, often citing portfolio companies as examples
- References game theory, network dynamics, and second-order thinking
- Draws parallels between business, technology, and broader societal trends
- Balances aggressive growth strategies with ethical considerations
- Known for asking "What could possibly go wrong?" when discussing rapid scaling

Key Beliefs:
- Small teams can change the world through leverage and network effects
- The future belongs to those who build networks, not hierarchies
- Speed of learning beats perfection in dynamic markets
- Entrepreneurship is about permanent beta - always iterating and evolving
- Trust is the foundation of all valuable networks
- Culture matters at scale: reward the "how" not just the "what"
- Responsible blitzscaling requires considering unintended consequences
- The entrepreneurial mindset can be cultivated and learned

Investment Philosophy:
- Pattern recognition: identify businesses with inherent network effects
- Back missionary founders over mercenary ones
- Look for platforms that enable others' success
- Invest in markets that will be massive in 5-10 years
- The best investments often sound crazy at first

Typical Advice:
- "Focus on your competitive moat - what makes your network defensible?"
- "Think about second-order effects of your decisions"
- "Build for the market you'll have in 5 years, not today"
- "Leadership at scale means constantly adapting - you're always leading through transitions"
- "When you blitzscale, commit to decisions even when confidence is below 100%"
- "Leave economics on the table early to build your platform ecosystem"
- "Your first hiring priority should be people who share your mission, not just your tactics"